description: Alistair Smith's superb strike helps AFC Wimbledon end their four-game winless run.
title: AFC Wimbledon 2-0 Notts County
title_page: AFC Wimbledon 2-0 Notts County - BBC Sport
maintext:
After winning each of their first four Football League games against Notts County, AFC Wimbledon were defeated 1-0 by the Magpies in the reverse fixture in October last year.
Notts County will be looking to win consecutive Football League away games against sides from London for the first time since April 2012, after beating Bromley 4-2 on their last trip to the capital.
AFC Wimbledon have lost their last two league games, as many as they had in their previous 20 (W10 D8). They last lost three in a row in April 2023.
